I Highly recommend this restaurant for the drinks. The drinks are delicious- tamarindo margarita and mango frozen margaritas are to die for. Enrique is the best waiter, not only is he affable and extremely attentive he is knowledgeable. I recommend this place for the drinks, just not the food.
Great date night spot. Love that they have churros on there menu.
Drinks were great. Food was good on thing my skirt steak was rare

Blue Agave doesn't disappoint... Great food, Good service, charming atmosphere (when indoor dining us allowed!!!) big backyard seating, wonderful cocktails!!!  Pro tip:  Blue Agave has a new kids lunch special for pickup & delivery... It's $8.99 & an awesome deal!!!
Excelente  Mexican Food delicious

I visit this lovely spot quite often! This is my favorite spot to eat.  I go there frequently. The meals are excellent, the crew is polite and the prices are good. I enjoy meeting in this spot over a decent supper.

I picked up a La Cantina lunch bowl from Blue Agave today and it was delicious. They have many choices for protein, toppings, sauces and even a build your own bowl option. The average lunch bowl is $11. The amount of food for the price was great and I was full and satisfied for hours. Definitely stop by if you’re looking for a quick and flavorful lunch.
(Translated by Google) Their food is good, but the drinks for me are honestly not good.  (Original) Su comida es buena , pero los tragos para mi  sinceramente  no son buenos..

Love the food, drinks, and staff at Blue Agave. We recently changed our diet to vegan, and we were so gracious for the delicious vegan options here, such as the vegan tacos, guac & chips, and the fried plantains. The vibe here is always fun but sort of low key.
Steak needed seasoning and the rest of our order was a bit cold.
Food was absolutely delicious! Just discovered my new Bay Ridge favorite!!!!
Great pork tacos and killer drinks. If you can't seat in front of their spot. There's a wooden structure used for holding flowers next door by the grocery to sit. Hahaha good deal.
Really good food with really friendly staff. Ordered the nachos, while my friend ordered a variety of tacos. Neither of us were disappointed at all.

My new favorite restaurant in Bay Ridge!! Service was great, the staff was so attentive but amidst that the food was exceptional. Authentic Mexican food and the drinks were even better, you must try the Hibiscus Margarita 😍 I will be coming here more often.
The tacos and empanadas here are always on point!

Pictured is a chicken quesadilla, bistec(steak, can't remember the rest of the name), chicken fajita w/fixings. The drink is a watermelon margarita. All great food & always friendly staff, in the patio area with nice ambiance.👍 The mashed potatoes weren't "bad", but could've used either garlic or cheese, preferably both.

I have been there several times since 2019, they’re friendly, fast, and consistent! Jorge is a great bartender. Recommended stuff for us to try. We mainly went for drinks and when I tried their food, my only regret was not doing it earlier! Fresh calamari. Not oily, rubbery. Crunchy and tasty. The chimichanga: I couldn’t just get one. They’re delicious. The flavor in the food is because of good cooking and  not over seasoning or overwhelming arrangements. You get what you order, and it’s going to be tasty Very accommodating for our group’s requests and always with a smile. It was the waitress’ first day but apart of looking slightly nervous (as anyone would during a first day anywhere) she was efficient, remembered our orders and made sure we were satisfied.  Sometimes you have to wait, but it’s worth it. Jorge will make sure your drinks are taken care of, and the rest of the staff will make you feel welcome.
Loved the authentic cultural food. The ambiance was nice
Enjoyed the best drinks ever with bartender Jorge Terreros in a clean and Covid safe environment. Love this place and the appetizers! 😀

Decide to go out for breakfast and I think I made a pretty good choice.. I didn't know they had a brunch menu with a nice variety to choose from it also included a drink of 3 choices such as Mimosa,Bellini or Screwdriver. I had The Huevos Rancheros part of the special with a Caphrina paid extra cause it wasn't part of the special but I knew this and that's what I wanted. I can say I enjoyed my brunch. I might just make it my weekly spot!!😀
Excellent Mexican food! Fresh, tasty and plentiful!
Most amazing service! Great food & drinks, well recommended.

Amazing food. Love their empanadas. One of the few places I feel safe taking my family to eat as the tables are actually 6 feet apart, staff wears mask, and you see them cleaning the tables with bleach after people are done eating. Staff wants you to enjoy yourself and have a good time.
THE FOOD IS AMAZING AND THE DRINKS TOO !! YOU DEF NEED TO COME THIS SPOT !! I'M COMING BACK FOR SURE !! THE OWNER IS A GREAT GUY, MUSIC IS GREAT !

What a great experience! We sat in the backyard and we loved the vibe. They played nice music and our server RICKY was awesome! Even though it was a little humid I had the best outdoor dinning (due to covid) experience so far. The privacy is nice. RICKY took care of us through the whole evening . We really loved the service we received from him! Such a friendly but professional person.  The food was great too! As we were looking through the menu we got complimentary chips and salsa. We ordered elote as an appetizer and were surprise at the big portion!! And it was full of flavor. My tacos were so juicy and my friend enjoyed her steak fajita. Although she said she would try the tacos instead next time.  Drinks came out perfect too. We ordered mojitos and the frozen margaritas were really refreshing on such a hot summer night.  We ended the dinner with a tres leches dessert. We thought it was OK. It definitely could use more condensed milk to make it more moist but it was delicious anyway.  I will definitely come back to this spot. Affordable. Great food , service &&& drinks.

I was a little disappointed with out experience here the other day. This was my favorite spot. I used to order out from here all the time before Covid and its my go to restaurant when family or friends are in town but I am not sure I will go back anytime soon. The waiter was super rude to us and we didn't get drinks or even water for a really long time. So long it came when the food did.  Another table noticed the rudness of the waiter. We mentioned it to him and he seemed to pick up the pace but it was a little too late for that. Then strangly at the end he kept coming by with things like napkins when are food was already gone. I get that he might of been having a bad day but I'm turned off from the place. Bad vibes with everything going on I would like to spend the experiences I do at places that welcome me.  It was my birthday too and they kind of ruined the celebration.
I like this place and the people who work here a lot, but I don’t understand why they don’t do brunch to go.
The two young ladies that assisted my daughter and I, couldn't care less. Very indifferent. We won't go back anytime soon.
Great cocktails
Watch your tabs they have a tendency to over charge they overcharged Me by 18 dollars two large Margaritas one regular and one spicy came out to $64
They FORGOT MY TORTILLAS WHATS A FAJITA WITHout TORTILLAS!!!!
Food was great. We were seated and served extremely fast.

A fun established restaurant in Bay Ridgee with many different tequilas, margaritas and mojitos. Really great and diverse menu with Mexican and Latin food. Drinks are fresh squeezed and delicious. Entrees are very fresh, try the fresh chorizo tacos!!! The owner was very friendly. A great experience, even for lunch!! (Had a lunch special and drink at the bar)
Wonderful Margaritas made with fresh fruit puree.   So yummy and reasonably priced.  Dinner was pretty good too although the ceviche could have used a little more seafood in it.
Small little Mexican spot. Nothing special, basic food, basic service.

This place isn’t that great. My husband took me there for my birthday brunch and the service was so slow! They gave us the wrong order, their mimosa special wasn’t provided the way we expected and the good was mediocre. Will not be going back.
Food consistent, service consiste9
Go here for flautas
Meat was dry and plain in flavor, second time trying the food and definitely there would not be a third time!!!
Jorge is an awesome bartender.
Small cozy place ideal for after office gatherings to drink truly delicious agave based cocktails and delicious mexican dishes.
Food was good and service was friendly.
Great food, drinks atmosphere and staff! Everybody is very friendly!
Great food
The food there was delicious and should be tried at least once!
Great food!
Great food!
Good food great place for a nice dinner

Margarita was great I had a hibiscus over ice, very delicious! I ordered 3 tacos steak, pork, and fish all was underwhelming! The fish was fried tilapia but it looked like two small strips of fish. No flavor for them I had to ask for hot sauce! A waste of $13
Food and drinks are great
Cocktails where good, but food was horrible. I personally think was from last year refrigerated food.
Great food/drinks and friendly attentive service.
Great food and margiritas.

I was here like a week ago and two weeks ago, so all together maybe like 3-4 times in a month. My wife and I realized how good it was and we kept going back. The food has amazing flavor! And the drinks are incredible. Let's say my favorite is the French Bulldog! But overall, the atmosphere is a very chill place and in the evening more live, because more people come in. The blue lighting in the front brings this attraction. I'm not to much of a picture person so my reviews never contain photos. Just take me word for it and believe me, you won't be disappointed.

Just okay. My husband and I were looking for a new place to try for Mexican food and we won't be back. I had a chicken fajita and he had the tacos..everything was very bland. The margarita was decent so there's that. I will say the waitstaff was friendly and attentive. If you're looking for good food and ambiance I'd say go elsewhere.
Drinks are amazing food is okay.

I was there for brunch with a party of 8. Got the Prix fix brunch, which was the best huevos rancheros I've ever had, and I've had many. We sat in the courtyard, which was cozy and created a great atmosphere. Highly recommended.

Horrible excuse for a Mexican restaurant. Why is it so hard to make fresh cook to order guacamole?? I asked the waiter is it fresh he confirms yes it is. Brings it out its ice cold straight out of the fridge to the point you can taste the tangy sourness that happens when you leave guac in the fridge to long. The burrito bowl was tasteless and bland and cubed like dog food. We asked to sit outside, it was a beautiful day and their response was only on the weekends. Unfathomable how this place is surviving. Save your money and time and go to Hobrah not to far away.
Delicious margaritas. Cute patio area.
Authentic food. Fantastic drinks.

Daniel definitely helped leave the best impression on this restaurant. My first time here and I loved the service so much, the food and drinks went out of this world with that! Thank you for the perfect ambiance !!!
This is my girlfriend favorite restaurant. Great drinks and food.

This is a cute little Mexican restaurant in Bay Ridge. Food and service is pretty good. My Raspberry Mojito was banging. I would definitely come again....I have to try one of the Margaritas on the menu.
Nice spot

Stopped for drinks. The margaritas did not disappoint.
A small place with a great atmosphere. Food and service was good. Would definitely go again.
The margaritas were good they have a great happy hour! The tostones with the garlic dip was delicious!
All of the food is an absolute hit. The waiter was incredibly kind and sociable. The space is small but well kept. Recommending it to everyone. 10/10

Relatively tiny this Mexican restaurant offers delicious food and drinks. Popular for its drinks Blue Agave have great Latin chicken and usual fare. The bar has stools for about 12 people. There is seating for about three dozen people in the restaurant. During the summer months there is a backyard. Blue Agave also has excellent delivery service. Highly recommended for intimate settings. It does get crowded weekend especially for brunch
This restaurant is quaint and has very good food
Love the food, particularly the avocado tacos. Great drinks and a good atmosphere. This is definitely my go to spot when I want Mexican food!
I organized my Holiday party for my staff. I spoke with the owners Dan and Frances. They worked with me , and Provided Excellent Food Service & Cocktails!!!
This place is consistently good. Service is excellent dining in and fast delivery . My favorite in the neighborhood.
Very nice spot to just get some good sushi and drink some rice wine!
Situation - Lunch on a Wednesday - I ordered the Super Chicken Burrito  Pros - The burrito was a great - The portion size of the burrito was really good - Not too bad of a prices for a super burrito.
Great food and drinks

Great service. Good food. Prices?

Good for the service and for the outdoor back patio. Food was ok, a little expensive for what you get. Go somewhere else for a cheap authentic Mexican restaurant though not as nice, like Las Margaritas across the street.

Great food, cool style , and great service. Worth a visit!
Good food, great drinks, late night music.
Delicious drinks, and good, affordable food. Airy, laid-back atmosphere, and helpful, responsive staff. Perfect place for a casual lunch or happy hour!
This place is great! There is a back patio and while you can bring your kid, it's a tight squeeze in winter. For all you nacho lovers out there, they have it and yes it's yummy.

One of the better Latin restaurants in Bay Ridge, the food aires on more a dominican flair, with everything being made in house. Their happy hour is great, $5 margaritas and imexpensive tapas. The shrimp amd jalapeno poppers are incredible, their roast chicken is some of the best in the city and the carne tacos are a must. Keep up the good work guys!

This place deserves more than 5 stars! Food is great, exceeded my expectations and service is more than I could ever expect in a small place like that. Atmosphere fantastic! Absolutely must visit even if you don’t live in the neighborhood
Cool place to chill and get your drink on.
DELICIOUS!

Consistently very good food and great cocktails! Love the Brunch menu - the Huevos a la Mexicana was so flavorful and delicious. One star off because the service was very slow on our last visit - no water/menu for about 15-20 min after we were seated and nobody checked on us to ask if we wanted anything else.

the spot love happy hour and brunch days but they did increase the price of the margs and more people been going

I looooooove thiis place.

Absolutely delicious. The chips and guacamole are addictive.
This place is good for drinks special, however I️ ordered chicken chimanga it had lot of rice and beans.
Strong margaritas and good food! Waiter was attentive and loved the atmosphere of the place.
The food here is really good. The service was good. Prices are decent and enough food to fill your belly. Drinks are great!
We went for dinner ,had nice outdoor seats in back .Great appetizers .Nice rasberry margaritas and Tacos huge buritos.Really good service nice staff .I was glad we stopped in .

All was good esp the veggie tacos until I found a long hair in my food. It was so gross. It was under and twisted into my food. They also mixed up two of my friends orders by serving the wrong burritos. Then our group of four had to continually call over our server when we needed something... I was hoping it would be better. The backyard seating was nice, however, I don’t think I’ll be going back.

Glass doors and blue lights welcome you into the small bar space in the front of the restaurant. There is a small seating area within the restaurant towards the back but I particularly enjoyed the garden seating in the backyard. The prices reflect that of Bay Ridge but you definitely get your money's worth in food. I order take out from here since I live nearby and the delivery is always quick.
The food was good and the staff was fantastic
This place was pretty average. The outside patio was nice. The ceviche was more like a salsa and didn't have enough lime, I'd skip it. The margaritas were good and strong.

For what you pay you really do not get a lot. I came in for dinner and got enchiladas, it was two enchiladas with a side of broccoli, I found it really weird that there was a side of broccoli, it was $17 and not enough food for one person. There are tons of really good Mexican restaurants, where you get great food for a good price. 2 tortillas with cheese and shrimp shouldn't run you 20 bucks
Great mexican food
Excellent quality food. Nice place to take your date. Have a really nice outdoor tables in the back yard during summer.
Food was great. .service too

Their food is ok at best. Appetizers aren't terrible, but for Latin food lacks the Latin rich flavor....However, if you want the most delicious and amazingly made drinks, THIS IS THE PLACE TO GO!!! Their drinks are probably one of the best out there!! We always come back for the friendly staff and amazing drinks!
Really quality food. Highly recommend the chorizo and my ultimate fave: the elote asado. Have been meaning to check out their brunch as well.
Love their chicken tostada salad. The drinks are great. The outdoor section is nice but I wish the indoor option had air conditioning.
Nachos, cocktails and a cute little backyard are my favorites :) Great with friends or a date. I would recommend happy hour.
Good food. Good service. Delicious lunch menu.

I found this restaurant when I wanted a place on Cinco de Mayo but never got to try. I've been wanting to try and glad I did. I got to have happy hour margaritas and they were good. I haven't had pozole in a long time so I had to try, and it was very good!  I wanted cerviche but they didn't have ready!  I asked if I could mix and match my tacos and it was allowed so I wanted carnitas and chorizo,  but they didn't have chorizo!  Since I wanted spicy waiter recommend tinga de pollo. They were excellent!  Be prepared for juices dripping down your arm! I needed endless amounts of napkins. I will definitely return.
Great food and drinks.  Excellent Happy You our Menu.  Friendly staff.
Great place
Fabulous drinks ,great guacamole , super attentive service what more can you ask for.

In a neighborhood flooded with Mexican restaurants, this is hands down THE BEST in Bay Ridge. Their margaritas are incredible. Their food is delicious. Especially the Pernil! They have amazing happy hours, drink specials and great guacamole. The service is excellent and timely. My wife and I go here probably once per week. Sometimes for dinner, and sometimes just to sit at the bar for a drink or two.
Amazing food !! Try shrimp tacos reminds me of Cali Mexican food
Good food

I love this place. Francis is a an amazing host and very receptive of customer needs. Although he's not as fast a runner as he claims to be.  Amazing food and amazing selection.

I've been here quite a few times since having moved here. I always get top-notch service and quality food. It certainly doesn't deserve less than four stars but I'm going to give it five. For their prices, the food is excellent and the staff makes it worth returning.
Cool place, can be a bit cramped if it's busy. Food's great and so are the drinks.

Excellent margaritas and great good to boot! Indoor and outdoor seating. Great for groups, welcoming to families with kids - an all-around solid Bay Ridge destination with a few other excellent restaurant neighbors (The Beet Company, Burger Bistro, Salud)

This place really changed after its rebranding. I used enjoy coming here with my family when it was named "Los Pollitos." The portions are small, and the steak I got was undercooked. Although they serve Hispanic food, it's obvious that theyre going for a more "trendy vibe" aimed towards a specific type of customers. It's overpriced too. I didn't give them one star because the waiter was courteous and attentive. This place is not worth your time if you want authentic Hispanic food. Definitely checking out "Las Margaritas" across the street the next time I'm eating in the area.
Very delicious margaritas and really yummy food. We also loved the outdoor area
Owner is always around. Great food. Great drinks
Their enchiladas verdes and chicken empanadas are delicious! They also make tasty micheladas! The music and vibe is pretty good every time we visit, not to mention the service.
Cozy place, very friendly staff. Guac was average, plantains and margaritas were very good. Chorizo quesadilla was awesome.
The food is fantastic. Love the nachos and chicken.

Came here with my wife for Brunch and I have to say the food is very tasty. Everything have flavor and they have great drinks specials.  The staff is very friendly and very attentive, I definitely recommend anyone to try this place. Keep up the good work guys.
